    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSet extmarks on unicode has strange behavior when `set spell`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/54128430/4c02f4ca-c7e1-49a4-878b-4c51cfd18552\r\n\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```text\r\n你好\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean test.txt`\r\n2. `:lua ns=vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"test\")`\r\n3. `:lua id=vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, {end_col=3,hl_group=\"Search\"})`, `你` has 3 bytes so I set the `end_col` to 3\r\n4. Now, only `你` is highlighted\r\n5. `:set spell`\r\n6. Now, both `你好` is highlighted\r\n7. `:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_del_extmark(0, ns, id)`\r\n8. `:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, {end_col=2,hl_group=\"Search\"})`, I set the `end_col` to 2 instead of 3\r\n9. Now, both `你好` is highlighted\r\n10. `:set nospell`\r\n11. Now, only `你` is highlighted\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOnly `你` is highlighted in step 6 and 9.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1974+g714b07519\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nunknown\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMicrosoft Windows 11 Home 10.0.22621 N/A Build 22621\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nempty\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop install neovim-nighlty --skip",
    "closed_at": "2023-12-28T11:27:01Z",
